article.headline: S.C. State 77, Md.-Eastern Shore 74
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Brian Mason scored a team-high 20 points and grabbed a game-high nine, and South Carolina State defeated Maryland-Eastern Shore, 77-74 Monday night. The game featured three ties and 13 lead changes. South Carolina State shot 48 percent from the field, compared with UMES' 42 percent. Jason Flagler came off the bench contributed 16 points for South Carolina State (9-13, 9-5 MEAC). Ed Tyson scored a game-high 37 points for UMES (3-20, 0-11). Milutin Mirajcic contributed eight rebounds.
